    <!-- ===================== SECTION FOURTEEN: Method of Intervals ===================== -->
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDef_5">Method of Intervals: find roots of P,Q; mark on axis; check signs; select valid intervals.</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDefQuestion_5">Using the method of intervals for (x−1)(x−3) &gt; 0, which value satisfies the inequality?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDefAnswerOne_5">2</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDefAnswerTwo_5">4</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDefAnswerThree_5">0</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_5">4</string>

    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryProperties_5">In the method of intervals: the sign of the expression alternates between consecutive roots for simple (odd-multiplicity) roots, and stays the same for even-multiplicity roots. Always verify endpoints separately for ≥ or ≤ inequalities.</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryPropsQuestion_5">For (x−2)²(x−5) &gt; 0, does the sign change at x = 2?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryPropsAnswerOne_5">True</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_5">False</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryPropsAnswerThree_5">Neither</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_5">False</string>

    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExamples_5">Example 1: Solve (x−1)(x−3) &gt; 0. Roots: 1 and 3. Sign chart: (+)(−)(+). Solution: (−∞,1) ∪ (3,+∞). \n
Example 2: Solve (x−2)(x+1) &lt; 0. Roots: −1 and 2. Sign chart: (+)(−)(+). Solution: (−1, 2). \n
Example 3: Solve (x−1)²(x−4) &gt; 0. Root x=1 (even mult.), root x=4. Sign same at x=1. Solution: (4, +∞). </string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExQuestion_5">How many roots does (x−1)(x−3) have on the number line for the method of intervals?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_5">1</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_5">2</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_5">3</string>
    <string name="SectionFourteenTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_5">2</string>

